Initiatory: To what extent did Part B reveal an event that preceded the Surprising Event chronologically and helped to cause the Surprising Event?
Deducible: To what extent would it have been possible for a reasonable person to predict the surprise given only the information in Part A?
Post-dictable: Now that you have the information in Part B, to what extent does the story make sense?
Important: From the perspective of the protagonist, how important were the events revealed in part B?
Valence: From the perspective of the protagonist, how positive (5) or negative (1) was the information revealed in part B?
Immutable: To what extent did the surprise contradict an expectation that was immutable, given the rules of the real world, or the established rules of the story?
